HEADWORD: Cubature
<hw>Cu"ba*ture</hw> <pr>(k?"b?-t?r; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cubus</ets> cube: cf. F. <ets>cubature</ets>. See
